300struct rocksdb_compactionfilter_t : public CompactionFilter {
301 void* state_;
302 void (*destructor_)(void*);
303 unsigned char (*filter_)(void*, int level, const char* key, size_t key_length,
304 const char* existing_value, size_t value_length,
305 char** new_value, size_t* new_value_length,
306 unsigned char* value_changed);
307 const char* (*name_)(void*);
308 unsigned char ignore_snapshots_;
309
310 ~rocksdb_compactionfilter_t() override { (*destructor_)(state_); }
311
312 bool Filter(int level, const Slice& key, const Slice& existing_value,
313 std::string* new_value, bool* value_changed) const override {
314 char* c_new_value = nullptr;
315 size_t new_value_length = 0;
316 unsigned char c_value_changed = 0;
317 unsigned char result =
318 (*filter_)(state_, level, key.data(), key.size(), existing_value.data(),
319 existing_value.size(), &c_new_value, &new_value_length,
320 &c_value_changed);
321 if (c_value_changed) {
322 new_value->assign(c_new_value, new_value_length);
323 *value_changed = true;
324 }
325 return result;
326 }
327
328 const char* Name() const override { return (*name_)(state_); }
329
330 bool IgnoreSnapshots() const override { return ignore_snapshots_; }
331};
332
333struct rocksdb_compactionfilterfactory_t : public CompactionFilterFactory {
334 void* state_;
335 void (*destructor_)(void*);
336 rocksdb_compactionfilter_t* (*create_compaction_filter_)(
337 void*, rocksdb_compactionfiltercontext_t* context);
338 const char* (*name_)(void*);
339
340 ~rocksdb_compactionfilterfactory_t() override { (*destructor_)(state_); }
341
342 std::unique_ptr<CompactionFilter> CreateCompactionFilter(
343 const CompactionFilter::Context& context) override {
344 rocksdb_compactionfiltercontext_t ccontext;
345 ccontext.rep = context;
346 CompactionFilter* cf = (*create_compaction_filter_)(state_, &ccontext);
347 return std::unique_ptr<CompactionFilter>(cf);
348 }
349
350 const char* Name() const override { return (*name_)(state_); }
351};
352
353struct rocksdb_comparator_t : public Comparator {
354 void* state_;
355 void (*destructor_)(void*);
356 int (*compare_)(void*, const char* a, size_t alen, const char* b,
357 size_t blen);
358 const char* (*name_)(void*);
359 int (*compare_ts_)(void*, const char* a_ts, size_t a_tslen, const char* b_ts,
360 size_t b_tslen);
361 int (*compare_without_ts_)(void*, const char* a, size_t alen,
362 unsigned char a_has_ts, const char* b, size_t blen,
363 unsigned char b_has_ts);
364
365 rocksdb_comparator_t() : Comparator() {}
366
367 rocksdb_comparator_t(size_t ts_size) : Comparator(ts_size) {}
368
369 ~rocksdb_comparator_t() override { (*destructor_)(state_); }
370
371 int Compare(const Slice& a, const Slice& b) const override {
372 return (*compare_)(state_, a.data(), a.size(), b.data(), b.size());
373 }
374
375 int CompareTimestamp(const Slice& a_ts, const Slice& b_ts) const override {
376 if (compare_ts_ == nullptr) {
377 return 0;
378 }
379 return (*compare_ts_)(state_, a_ts.data(), a_ts.size(), b_ts.data(),
380 b_ts.size());
381 }
382
383 int CompareWithoutTimestamp(const Slice& a, bool a_has_ts, const Slice& b,
384 bool b_has_ts) const override {
385 if (compare_without_ts_ == nullptr) {
386 return Compare(a, b);
387 }
388 return (*compare_without_ts_)(state_, a.data(), a.size(), a_has_ts,
389 b.data(), b.size(), b_has_ts);
390 }
391
392 const char* Name() const override { return (*name_)(state_); }
393
394 // No-ops since the C binding does not support key shortening methods.
395 void FindShortestSeparator(std::string*, const Slice&) const override {}
396 void FindShortSuccessor(std::string* /*key*/) const override {}
397};

409struct rocksdb_mergeoperator_t : public MergeOperator {
410 void* state_;
411 void (*destructor_)(void*);
412 const char* (*name_)(void*);
413 char* (*full_merge_)(void*, const char* key, size_t key_length,
414 const char* existing_value, size_t existing_value_length,
415 const char* const* operands_list,
416 const size_t* operands_list_length, int num_operands,
417 unsigned char* success, size_t* new_value_length);
418 char* (*partial_merge_)(void*, const char* key, size_t key_length,
419 const char* const* operands_list,
420 const size_t* operands_list_length, int num_operands,
421 unsigned char* success, size_t* new_value_length);
422 void (*delete_value_)(void*, const char* value, size_t value_length);
423
424 ~rocksdb_mergeoperator_t() override { (*destructor_)(state_); }
425
426 const char* Name() const override { return (*name_)(state_); }
427
428 bool FullMergeV2(const MergeOperationInput& merge_in,
429 MergeOperationOutput* merge_out) const override {
430 size_t n = merge_in.operand_list.size();
431 std::vector<const char*> operand_pointers(n);
432 std::vector<size_t> operand_sizes(n);
433 for (size_t i = 0; i < n; i++) {
434 Slice operand(merge_in.operand_list[i]);
435 operand_pointers[i] = operand.data();
436 operand_sizes[i] = operand.size();
437 }
438
439 const char* existing_value_data = nullptr;
440 size_t existing_value_len = 0;
441 if (merge_in.existing_value != nullptr) {
442 existing_value_data = merge_in.existing_value->data();
443 existing_value_len = merge_in.existing_value->size();
444 }
445
446 unsigned char success;
447 size_t new_value_len;
448 char* tmp_new_value = (*full_merge_)(
449 state_, merge_in.key.data(), merge_in.key.size(), existing_value_data,
450 existing_value_len, operand_pointers.data(), operand_sizes.data(),
451 static_cast<int>(n), &success, &new_value_len);
452 merge_out->new_value.assign(tmp_new_value, new_value_len);
453
454 if (delete_value_ != nullptr) {
455 (*delete_value_)(state_, tmp_new_value, new_value_len);
456 } else {
457 free(tmp_new_value);
458 }
459
460 return success;
461 }
462
463 bool PartialMergeMulti(const Slice& key,
464 const std::deque<Slice>& operand_list,
465 std::string* new_value,
466 Logger* /*logger*/) const override {
467 size_t operand_count = operand_list.size();
468 std::vector<const char*> operand_pointers(operand_count);
469 std::vector<size_t> operand_sizes(operand_count);
470 for (size_t i = 0; i < operand_count; ++i) {
471 Slice operand(operand_list[i]);
472 operand_pointers[i] = operand.data();
473 operand_sizes[i] = operand.size();
474 }
475
476 unsigned char success;
477 size_t new_value_len;
478 char* tmp_new_value = (*partial_merge_)(
479 state_, key.data(), key.size(), operand_pointers.data(),
480 operand_sizes.data(), static_cast<int>(operand_count), &success,
481 &new_value_len);
482 new_value->assign(tmp_new_value, new_value_len);
483
484 if (delete_value_ != nullptr) {
485 (*delete_value_)(state_, tmp_new_value, new_value_len);
486 } else {
487 free(tmp_new_value);
488 }
489
490 return success;
491 }
492};

503struct rocksdb_slicetransform_t : public SliceTransform {
504 void* state_;
505 void (*destructor_)(void*);
506 const char* (*name_)(void*);
507 char* (*transform_)(void*, const char* key, size_t length,
508 size_t* dst_length);
509 unsigned char (*in_domain_)(void*, const char* key, size_t length);
510 unsigned char (*in_range_)(void*, const char* key, size_t length);
511
512 ~rocksdb_slicetransform_t() override { (*destructor_)(state_); }
513
514 const char* Name() const override { return (*name_)(state_); }
515
516 Slice Transform(const Slice& src) const override {
517 size_t len;
518 char* dst = (*transform_)(state_, src.data(), src.size(), &len);
519 return Slice(dst, len);
520 }
521
522 bool InDomain(const Slice& src) const override {
523 return (*in_domain_)(state_, src.data(), src.size());
524 }
525
526 bool InRange(const Slice& src) const override {
527 return (*in_range_)(state_, src.data(), src.size());
528 }
529};

535struct rocksdb_callback_logger_t : public Logger {
536 static const ssize_t STACK_BUFSZ = 512;
537 rocksdb_callback_logger_t(InfoLogLevel log_level,
538 void (*logv_cb)(void*, unsigned, char*, size_t),
539 void* priv)
540 : Logger(log_level), logv_cb_(logv_cb), priv_(priv) {}
541
542 using Logger::Logv;
543 void Logv(const InfoLogLevel level, const char* fmt, va_list ap0) override {
544 char stack_buf[STACK_BUFSZ];
545 char* alloc_buf = nullptr;
546 char* buf = stack_buf;
547 int len = 0;
548 va_list ap1;
549 if (!logv_cb_) return;
550 va_copy(ap1, ap0);
551 len = vsnprintf(buf, STACK_BUFSZ, fmt, ap0);
552 if (len <= 0)
553 goto cleanup;
554 else if (len >= STACK_BUFSZ) {
555 buf = alloc_buf = reinterpret_cast<char*>(malloc(len + 1));
556 if (!buf) goto cleanup;
557 len = vsnprintf(buf, len + 1, fmt, ap1);
558 if (len <= 0) goto cleanup;
559 }
560 logv_cb_(priv_, unsigned(level), buf, size_t(len));
561 cleanup:
562 va_end(ap1);
563 free(alloc_buf);
564 }
565
566 private:
567 void (*logv_cb_)(void*, unsigned, char*, size_t) = nullptr;
568 void* priv_ = nullptr;
569};
570
571static bool SaveError(char** errptr, const Status& s) {
572 assert(errptr != nullptr);
573 if (s.ok()) {
574 return false;
575 } else if (*errptr == nullptr) {
576 *errptr = strdup(s.ToString().c_str());
577 } else {
578 // TODO(sanjay): Merge with existing error?
579 // This is a bug if *errptr is not created by malloc()
580 free(*errptr);
581 *errptr = strdup(s.ToString().c_str());
582 }
583 return true;
584}
585
586// Copies str to a new malloc()-ed buffer. The buffer is not NUL terminated.
587static char* CopyString(const std::string& str) {
588 char* result = reinterpret_cast<char*>(malloc(sizeof(char) * str.size()));
589 memcpy(result, str.data(), sizeof(char) * str.size());
590 return result;
591}
592
593rocksdb_t* rocksdb_open(const rocksdb_options_t* options, const char* name,
594 char** errptr) {
595 DB* db;
596 if (SaveError(errptr, DB::Open(options->rep, std::string(name), &db))) {
597 return nullptr;
598 }
599 rocksdb_t* result = new rocksdb_t;
600 result->rep = db;
601 return result;
602}
603
604rocksdb_t* rocksdb_open_with_ttl(const rocksdb_options_t* options,
605 const char* name, int ttl, char** errptr) {
606 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::DBWithTTL* db;
607 if (SaveError(errptr, ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::DBWithTTL::Open(
608 options->rep, std::string(name), &db, ttl))) {
609 return nullptr;
610 }
611 rocksdb_t* result = new rocksdb_t;
612 result->rep = db;
613 return result;
614}

616rocksdb_t* rocksdb_open_for_read_only(const rocksdb_options_t* options,
617 const char* name,
618 unsigned char error_if_wal_file_exists,
619 char** errptr) {
620 DB* db;
621 if (SaveError(errptr, DB::OpenForReadOnly(options->rep, std::string(name),
622 &db, error_if_wal_file_exists))) {
623 return nullptr;
624 }
625 rocksdb_t* result = new rocksdb_t;
626 result->rep = db;
627 return result;
628}

630rocksdb_t* rocksdb_open_as_secondary(const rocksdb_options_t* options,
631 const char* name,
632 const char* secondary_path,
633 char** errptr) {
634 DB* db;
635 if (SaveError(errptr,
636 DB::OpenAsSecondary(options->rep, std::string(name),
637 std::string(secondary_path), &db))) {
638 return nullptr;
639 }
640 rocksdb_t* result = new rocksdb_t;
641 result->rep = db;
642 return result;
643}

645rocksdb_backup_engine_t* rocksdb_backup_engine_open(
646 const rocksdb_options_t* options, const char* path, char** errptr) {
647 BackupEngine* be;
648 if (SaveError(errptr, BackupEngine::Open(
649 options->rep.env,
650 BackupEngineOptions(path, nullptr, true,
651 options->rep.info_log.get()),
652 &be))) {
653 return nullptr;
654 }
655 rocksdb_backup_engine_t* result = new rocksdb_backup_engine_t;
656 result->rep = be;
657 return result;
658}

919
920rocksdb_t* rocksdb_open_and_trim_history(
921 const rocksdb_options_t* db_options, const char* name,
922 int num_column_families, const char* const* column_family_names,
923 const rocksdb_options_t* const* column_family_options,
924 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t** column_family_handles, char* trim_ts,
925 size_t trim_tslen, char** errptr) {
926 std::vector<ColumnFamilyDescriptor> column_families;
927 for (int i = 0; i < num_column_families; i++) {
928 column_families.emplace_back(
929 std::string(column_family_names[i]),
930 ColumnFamilyOptions(column_family_options[i]->rep));
931 }
932
933 std::string trim_ts_(trim_ts, trim_tslen);
934
935 DB* db;
936 std::vector<ColumnFamilyHandle*> handles;
937 if (SaveError(errptr, DB::OpenAndTrimHistory(
938 DBOptions(db_options->rep), std::string(name),
939 column_families, &handles, &db, trim_ts_))) {
940 return nullptr;
941 }
942
943 for (size_t i = 0; i < handles.size(); i++) {
944 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* c_handle =
945 new rocksdb_column_family_handle_t;
946 c_handle->rep = handles[i];
947 c_handle->immortal = false;
948 column_family_handles[i] = c_handle;
949 }
950 rocksdb_t* result = new rocksdb_t;
951 result->rep = db;
952 return result;
953}
954
955rocksdb_t* rocksdb_open_column_families(
956 const rocksdb_options_t* db_options, const char* name,
957 int num_column_families, const char* const* column_family_names,
958 const rocksdb_options_t* const* column_family_options,
959 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t** column_family_handles, char** errptr) {
960 std::vector<ColumnFamilyDescriptor> column_families;
961 for (int i = 0; i < num_column_families; i++) {
962 column_families.emplace_back(
963 std::string(column_family_names[i]),
964 ColumnFamilyOptions(column_family_options[i]->rep));
965 }
966
967 DB* db;
968 std::vector<ColumnFamilyHandle*> handles;
969 if (SaveError(errptr, DB::Open(DBOptions(db_options->rep), std::string(name),
970 column_families, &handles, &db))) {
971 return nullptr;
972 }
973
974 for (size_t i = 0; i < handles.size(); i++) {
975 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* c_handle =
976 new rocksdb_column_family_handle_t;
977 c_handle->rep = handles[i];
978 c_handle->immortal = false;
979 column_family_handles[i] = c_handle;
980 }
981 rocksdb_t* result = new rocksdb_t;
982 result->rep = db;
983 return result;
984}
985
986rocksdb_t* rocksdb_open_column_families_with_ttl(
987 const rocksdb_options_t* db_options, const char* name,
988 int num_column_families, const char* const* column_family_names,
989 const rocksdb_options_t* const* column_family_options,
990 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t** column_family_handles, const int* ttls,
991 char** errptr) {
992 std::vector<int32_t> ttls_vec;
993 std::vector<ColumnFamilyDescriptor> column_families;
994 for (int i = 0; i < num_column_families; i++) {
995 ttls_vec.push_back(ttls[i]);
996
997 column_families.emplace_back(
998 std::string(column_family_names[i]),
999 ColumnFamilyOptions(column_family_options[i]->rep));
1000 }
1001
1002 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::DBWithTTL* db;
1003 std::vector<ColumnFamilyHandle*> handles;
1004 if (SaveError(errptr, ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::DBWithTTL::Open(
1005 DBOptions(db_options->rep), std::string(name),
1006 column_families, &handles, &db, ttls_vec))) {
1007 return nullptr;
1008 }
1009
1010 for (size_t i = 0; i < handles.size(); i++) {
1011 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* c_handle =
1012 new rocksdb_column_family_handle_t;
1013 c_handle->rep = handles[i];
1014 c_handle->immortal = false;
1015 column_family_handles[i] = c_handle;
1016 }
1017 rocksdb_t* result = new rocksdb_t;
1018 result->rep = db;
1019 return result;
1020}

1022rocksdb_t* rocksdb_open_for_read_only_column_families(
1023 const rocksdb_options_t* db_options, const char* name,
1024 int num_column_families, const char* const* column_family_names,
1025 const rocksdb_options_t* const* column_family_options,

1032 ColumnFamilyOptions(column_family_options[i]->rep));
1033 }
1034
1035 DB* db;
1036 std::vector<ColumnFamilyHandle*> handles;
1037 if (SaveError(errptr,
1038 DB::OpenForReadOnly(DBOptions(db_options->rep),
1039 std::string(name), column_families,
1040 &handles, &db, error_if_wal_file_exists))) {
1041 return nullptr;
1042 }
1043
1044 for (size_t i = 0; i < handles.size(); i++) {
1045 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* c_handle =
1046 new rocksdb_column_family_handle_t;
1047 c_handle->rep = handles[i];
1048 c_handle->immortal = false;
1049 column_family_handles[i] = c_handle;

1052 result->rep = db;
1053 return result;
1054}

1056rocksdb_t* rocksdb_open_as_secondary_column_families(
1057 const rocksdb_options_t* db_options, const char* name,
1058 const char* secondary_path, int num_column_families,
1059 const char* const* column_family_names,
1060 const rocksdb_options_t* const* column_family_options,
1061 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t** column_family_handles, char** errptr) {
1062 std::vector<ColumnFamilyDescriptor> column_families;
1063 for (int i = 0; i != num_column_families; ++i) {
1064 column_families.emplace_back(
1065 std::string(column_family_names[i]),
1066 ColumnFamilyOptions(column_family_options[i]->rep));
1067 }
1068 DB* db;
1069 std::vector<ColumnFamilyHandle*> handles;
1070 if (SaveError(errptr, DB::OpenAsSecondary(DBOptions(db_options->rep),
1071 std::string(name),
1072 std::string(secondary_path),
1073 column_families, &handles, &db))) {
1074 return nullptr;
1075 }
1076 for (size_t i = 0; i != handles.size(); ++i) {
1077 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* c_handle =
1078 new rocksdb_column_family_handle_t;
1079 c_handle->rep = handles[i];
1080 c_handle->immortal = false;
1081 column_family_handles[i] = c_handle;
1082 }
1083 rocksdb_t* result = new rocksdb_t;
1084 result->rep = db;
1085 return result;
1086}
1087
1088char** rocksdb_list_column_families(const rocksdb_options_t* options,
1089 const char* name, size_t* lencfs,
1090 char** errptr) {
1091 std::vector<std::string> fams;
1092 SaveError(errptr, DB::ListColumnFamilies(DBOptions(options->rep),
1093 std::string(name), &fams));
1094
1095 *lencfs = fams.size();
1096 char** column_families =
1097 static_cast<char**>(malloc(sizeof(char*) * fams.size()));
1098 for (size_t i = 0; i < fams.size(); i++) {
1099 column_families[i] = strdup(fams[i].c_str());
1100 }
1101 return column_families;
1102}
1103
1104void rocksdb_list_column_families_destroy(char** list, size_t len) {
1105 for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i) {
1106 free(list[i]);
1107 }
1108 free(list);
1109}
1110
1111rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* rocksdb_create_column_family(
1112 rocksdb_t* db, const rocksdb_options_t* column_family_options,
1113 const char* column_family_name, char** errptr) {
1114 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* handle = new rocksdb_column_family_handle_t;
1115 SaveError(errptr, db->rep->CreateColumnFamily(
1116 ColumnFamilyOptions(column_family_options->rep),
1117 std::string(column_family_name), &(handle->rep)));
1118 handle->immortal = false;
1119 return handle;
1120}
1121
1122rocksdb_column_family_handle_t** rocksdb_create_column_families(
1123 rocksdb_t* db, const rocksdb_options_t* column_family_options,
1124 int num_column_families, const char* const* column_family_names,
1125 size_t* lencfs, char** errptr) {
1126 std::vector<ColumnFamilyHandle*> handles;
1127 std::vector<std::string> names;
1128 for (int i = 0; i != num_column_families; ++i) {
1129 names.emplace_back(column_family_names[i]);
1130 }
1131 SaveError(errptr, db->rep->CreateColumnFamilies(
1132 ColumnFamilyOptions(column_family_options->rep), names,
1133 &handles));
1134
1135 *lencfs = handles.size();
1136 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t** c_handles =
1137 static_cast<rocksdb_column_family_handle_t**>(
1138 malloc(sizeof(rocksdb_column_family_handle_t*) * handles.size()));
1139 for (size_t i = 0; i != handles.size(); ++i) {
1140 c_handles[i] = new rocksdb_column_family_handle_t;
1141 c_handles[i]->rep = handles[i];
1142 c_handles[i]->immortal = false;
1143 }
1144
1145 return c_handles;
1146}
1147
1148void rocksdb_create_column_families_destroy(
1149 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t** list) {
1150 free(list);
1151}
1152
1153rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* rocksdb_create_column_family_with_ttl(
1154 rocksdb_t* db, const rocksdb_options_t* column_family_options,
1155 const char* column_family_name, int ttl, char** errptr) {
1156 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::DBWithTTL* db_with_ttl =
1157 static_cast<ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::DBWithTTL*>(db->rep);
1158 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* handle = new rocksdb_column_family_handle_t;
1159 SaveError(errptr, db_with_ttl->CreateColumnFamilyWithTtl(
1160 ColumnFamilyOptions(column_family_options->rep),
1161 std::string(column_family_name), &(handle->rep), ttl));
1162 handle->immortal = false;
1163 return handle;
1164}

1239void rocksdb_delete_cf(rocksdb_t* db, const rocksdb_writeoptions_t* options,
1240 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* column_family,

1347char* rocksdb_get(rocksdb_t* db, const rocksdb_readoptions_t* options,
1348 const char* key, size_t keylen, size_t* vallen,
1349 char** errptr) {
1350 char* result = nullptr;

1352 Status s = db->rep->Get(options->rep, Slice(key, keylen), &tmp);
1353 if (s.ok()) {
1354 *vallen = tmp.size();
1355 result = CopyString(tmp);
1356 } else {
1357 *vallen = 0;
1358 if (!s.IsNotFound()) {
1359 SaveError(errptr, s);
1360 }
1361 }
1362 return result;

1396 *ts = CopyString(tmp_ts);
1397 } else {
1398 *vallen = 0;
1399 *tslen = 0;
1400 if (!s.IsNotFound()) {
1401 SaveError(errptr, s);
1402 }
1403 }
1404 return result;

1443
1444void rocksdb_multi_get(rocksdb_t* db, const rocksdb_readoptions_t* options,
1445 size_t num_keys, const char* const* keys_list,
1446 const size_t* keys_list_sizes, char** values_list,
1447 size_t* values_list_sizes, char** errs) {
1448 std::vector<Slice> keys(num_keys);
1449 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_keys; i++) {
1450 keys[i] = Slice(keys_list[i], keys_list_sizes[i]);
1451 }
1452 std::vector<std::string> values(num_keys);
1453 std::vector<Status> statuses = db->rep->MultiGet(options->rep, keys, &values);
1454 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_keys; i++) {
1455 if (statuses[i].ok()) {
1456 values_list[i] = CopyString(values[i]);
1457 values_list_sizes[i] = values[i].size();
1458 errs[i] = nullptr;
1459 } else {
1460 values_list[i] = nullptr;
1461 values_list_sizes[i] = 0;
1462 if (!statuses[i].IsNotFound()) {
1463 errs[i] = strdup(statuses[i].ToString().c_str());
1464 } else {
1465 errs[i] = nullptr;
1466 }
1467 }
1468 }
1469}
1470
1471void rocksdb_multi_get_with_ts(rocksdb_t* db,
1472 const rocksdb_readoptions_t* options,
1473 size_t num_keys, const char* const* keys_list,
1474 const size_t* keys_list_sizes,
1475 char** values_list, size_t* values_list_sizes,
1476 char** timestamp_list,
1477 size_t* timestamp_list_sizes, char** errs) {
1478 std::vector<Slice> keys(num_keys);
1479 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_keys; i++) {
1480 keys[i] = Slice(keys_list[i], keys_list_sizes[i]);
1481 }
1482 std::vector<std::string> values(num_keys);
1483 std::vector<std::string> timestamps(num_keys);
1484 std::vector<Status> statuses =
1485 db->rep->MultiGet(options->rep, keys, &values, &timestamps);
1486 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_keys; i++) {
1487 if (statuses[i].ok()) {
1488 values_list[i] = CopyString(values[i]);
1489 values_list_sizes[i] = values[i].size();
1490 timestamp_list[i] = CopyString(timestamps[i]);
1491 timestamp_list_sizes[i] = timestamps[i].size();
1492 errs[i] = nullptr;
1493 } else {
1494 values_list[i] = nullptr;
1495 values_list_sizes[i] = 0;
1496 timestamp_list[i] = nullptr;
1497 timestamp_list_sizes[i] = 0;
1498 if (!statuses[i].IsNotFound()) {
1499 errs[i] = strdup(statuses[i].ToString().c_str());
1500 } else {
1501 errs[i] = nullptr;
1502 }
1503 }
1504 }
1505}

1507void rocksdb_multi_get_cf(
1508 rocksdb_t* db, const rocksdb_readoptions_t* options,
1509 const rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* const* column_families,
1510 size_t num_keys, const char* const* keys_list,
1511 const size_t* keys_list_sizes, char** values_list,
1512 size_t* values_list_sizes, char** errs) {
1513 std::vector<Slice> keys(num_keys);
1514 std::vector<ColumnFamilyHandle*> cfs(num_keys);
1515 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_keys; i++) {
1516 keys[i] = Slice(keys_list[i], keys_list_sizes[i]);
1517 cfs[i] = column_families[i]->rep;
1518 }
1519 std::vector<std::string> values(num_keys);
1520 std::vector<Status> statuses =
1521 db->rep->MultiGet(options->rep, cfs, keys, &values);
1522 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_keys; i++) {
1523 if (statuses[i].ok()) {
1524 values_list[i] = CopyString(values[i]);
1525 values_list_sizes[i] = values[i].size();
1526 errs[i] = nullptr;
1527 } else {
1528 values_list[i] = nullptr;
1529 values_list_sizes[i] = 0;
1530 if (!statuses[i].IsNotFound()) {
1531 errs[i] = strdup(statuses[i].ToString().c_str());
1532 } else {
1533 errs[i] = nullptr;
1534 }
1535 }
1536 }
1537}

1539void rocksdb_multi_get_cf_with_ts(
1540 rocksdb_t* db, const rocksdb_readoptions_t* options,
1541 const rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* const* column_families,
1542 size_t num_keys, const char* const* keys_list,
1543 const size_t* keys_list_sizes, char** values_list,
1544 size_t* values_list_sizes, char** timestamps_list,
1545 size_t* timestamps_list_sizes, char** errs) {
1546 std::vector<Slice> keys(num_keys);
1547 std::vector<ColumnFamilyHandle*> cfs(num_keys);
1548 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_keys; i++) {
1549 keys[i] = Slice(keys_list[i], keys_list_sizes[i]);
1550 cfs[i] = column_families[i]->rep;
1551 }
1552 std::vector<std::string> values(num_keys);
1553 std::vector<std::string> timestamps(num_keys);
1554 std::vector<Status> statuses =
1555 db->rep->MultiGet(options->rep, cfs, keys, &values, &timestamps);
1556 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_keys; i++) {
1557 if (statuses[i].ok()) {
1558 values_list[i] = CopyString(values[i]);
1559 values_list_sizes[i] = values[i].size();
1560 timestamps_list[i] = CopyString(timestamps[i]);
1561 timestamps_list_sizes[i] = timestamps[i].size();
1562 errs[i] = nullptr;
1563 } else {
1564 values_list[i] = nullptr;
1565 values_list_sizes[i] = 0;
1566 timestamps_list[i] = nullptr;
1567 timestamps_list_sizes[i] = 0;
1568 if (!statuses[i].IsNotFound()) {
1569 errs[i] = strdup(statuses[i].ToString().c_str());
1570 } else {
1571 errs[i] = nullptr;
1572 }
1573 }
1574 }
1575}
1576
1577void rocksdb_batched_multi_get_cf(rocksdb_t* db,
1578 const rocksdb_readoptions_t* options,
1579 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* column_family,
1580 size_t num_keys, const char* const* keys_list,
1581 const size_t* keys_list_sizes,
1582 rocksdb_pinnableslice_t** values, char** errs,
1583 const bool sorted_input) {
1584 Slice* key_slices = new Slice[num_keys];
1585 PinnableSlice* value_slices = new PinnableSlice[num_keys];
1586 Status* statuses = new Status[num_keys];
1587 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_keys; ++i) {
1588 key_slices[i] = Slice(keys_list[i], keys_list_sizes[i]);
1589 }
1590
1591 db->rep->MultiGet(options->rep, column_family->rep, num_keys, key_slices,
1592 value_slices, statuses, sorted_input);
1593
1594 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_keys; ++i) {
1595 if (statuses[i].ok()) {
1596 values[i] = new (rocksdb_pinnableslice_t);
1597 values[i]->rep = std::move(value_slices[i]);
1598 errs[i] = nullptr;
1599 } else {
1600 values[i] = nullptr;
1601 if (!statuses[i].IsNotFound()) {
1602 errs[i] = strdup(statuses[i].ToString().c_str());
1603 } else {
1604 errs[i] = nullptr;
1605 }
1606 }
1607 }
1608
1609 delete[] key_slices;
1610 delete[] value_slices;
1611 delete[] statuses;
1612}
1613
1614unsigned char rocksdb_key_may_exist(rocksdb_t* db,
1615 const rocksdb_readoptions_t* options,
1616 const char* key, size_t key_len,
1617 char** value, size_t* val_len,
1618 const char* timestamp, size_t timestamp_len,
1619 unsigned char* value_found) {
1620 std::string tmp;
1621 std::string time;
1622 if (timestamp) {
1623 time.assign(timestamp, timestamp_len);
1624 }
1625 bool found = false;
1626 const bool result = db->rep->KeyMayExist(options->rep, Slice(key, key_len),
1627 &tmp, timestamp ? &time : nullptr,
1628 value_found ? &found : nullptr);
1629 if (value_found) {
1630 *value_found = found;
1631 if (found) {
1632 *val_len = tmp.size();
1633 *value = CopyString(tmp);
1634 }
1635 }
1636 return result;
1637}
1638
1639unsigned char rocksdb_key_may_exist_cf(
1640 rocksdb_t* db, const rocksdb_readoptions_t* options,
1641 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* column_family, const char* key,
1642 size_t key_len, char** value, size_t* val_len, const char* timestamp,
1643 size_t timestamp_len, unsigned char* value_found) {
1644 std::string tmp;
1645 std::string time;
1646 if (timestamp) {
1647 time.assign(timestamp, timestamp_len);
1648 }
1649 bool found = false;
1650 const bool result = db->rep->KeyMayExist(
1651 options->rep, column_family->rep, Slice(key, key_len), &tmp,
1652 timestamp ? &time : nullptr, value_found ? &found : nullptr);
1653 if (value_found) {
1654 *value_found = found;
1655 if (found) {
1656 *val_len = tmp.size();
1657 *value = CopyString(tmp);
1658 }
1659 }
1660 return result;
1661}

1663rocksdb_iterator_t* rocksdb_create_iterator(
1664 rocksdb_t* db, const rocksdb_readoptions_t* options) {
1665 rocksdb_iterator_t* result = new rocksdb_iterator_t;
1666 result->rep = db->rep->NewIterator(options->rep);

1669
1670rocksdb_wal_iterator_t* rocksdb_get_updates_since(
1671 rocksdb_t* db, uint64_t seq_number,
1672 const rocksdb_wal_readoptions_t* options, char** errptr) {
1673 std::unique_ptr<TransactionLogIterator> iter;
1674 TransactionLogIterator::ReadOptions ro;
1675 if (options != nullptr) {
1676 ro = options->rep;
1677 }
1678 if (SaveError(errptr, db->rep->GetUpdatesSince(seq_number, &iter, ro))) {
1679 return nullptr;
1680 }
1681 rocksdb_wal_iterator_t* result = new rocksdb_wal_iterator_t;
1682 result->rep = iter.release();
1683 return result;
1684}
1685
1686void rocksdb_wal_iter_next(rocksdb_wal_iterator_t* iter) { iter->rep->Next(); }
1687
1688unsigned char rocksdb_wal_iter_valid(const rocksdb_wal_iterator_t* iter) {
1689 return iter->rep->Valid();
1690}
1691
1692void rocksdb_wal_iter_status(const rocksdb_wal_iterator_t* iter,
1693 char** errptr) {
1694 SaveError(errptr, iter->rep->status());
1695}
1696
1697void rocksdb_wal_iter_destroy(const rocksdb_wal_iterator_t* iter) {
1698 delete iter->rep;
1699 delete iter;
1700}
1701
1702rocksdb_writebatch_t* rocksdb_wal_iter_get_batch(
1703 const rocksdb_wal_iterator_t* iter, uint64_t* seq) {
1704 rocksdb_writebatch_t* result = rocksdb_writebatch_create();
1705 BatchResult wal_batch = iter->rep->GetBatch();
1706 result->rep = std::move(*wal_batch.writeBatchPtr);
1707 if (seq != nullptr) {
1708 *seq = wal_batch.sequence;
1709 }
1710 return result;
1711}

1714 return db->rep->GetLatestSequenceNumber();
1715}

1717rocksdb_iterator_t* rocksdb_create_iterator_cf(
1718 rocksdb_t* db, const rocksdb_readoptions_t* options,
1719 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* column_family) {
1720 rocksdb_iterator_t* result = new rocksdb_iterator_t;
1721 result->rep = db->rep->NewIterator(options->rep, column_family->rep);
1722 return result;
1723}
1724
1725void rocksdb_create_iterators(rocksdb_t* db, rocksdb_readoptions_t* opts,
1726 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t** column_families,
1727 rocksdb_iterator_t** iterators, size_t size,
1728 char** errptr) {
1729 std::vector<ColumnFamilyHandle*> column_families_vec;
1730 for (size_t i = 0; i < size; i++) {
1731 column_families_vec.push_back(column_families[i]->rep);
1732 }
1733
1734 std::vector<Iterator*> res;
1735 Status status = db->rep->NewIterators(opts->rep, column_families_vec, &res);
1736 assert(res.size() == size);
1737 if (SaveError(errptr, status)) {
1738 return;
1739 }
1740
1741 for (size_t i = 0; i < size; i++) {
1742 iterators[i] = new rocksdb_iterator_t;
1743 iterators[i]->rep = res[i];
1744 }
1745}

1768 return strdup(tmp.c_str());

1770 return nullptr;
1771 }
1772}

1804
1805void rocksdb_approximate_sizes(rocksdb_t* db, int num_ranges,
1806 const char* const* range_start_key,
1807 const size_t* range_start_key_len,
1808 const char* const* range_limit_key,
1809 const size_t* range_limit_key_len,
1810 uint64_t* sizes, char** errptr) {
1811 Range* ranges = new Range[num_ranges];
1812 for (int i = 0; i < num_ranges; i++) {
1813 ranges[i].start = Slice(range_start_key[i], range_start_key_len[i]);
1814 ranges[i].limit = Slice(range_limit_key[i], range_limit_key_len[i]);
1815 }
1816 Status s = db->rep->GetApproximateSizes(ranges, num_ranges, sizes);
1817 if (!s.ok()) {
1818 SaveError(errptr, s);
1819 }
1820 delete[] ranges;
1821}
1822
1823void rocksdb_approximate_sizes_cf(
1824 rocksdb_t* db, rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* column_family,
1825 int num_ranges, const char* const* range_start_key,
1826 const size_t* range_start_key_len, const char* const* range_limit_key,
1827 const size_t* range_limit_key_len, uint64_t* sizes, char** errptr) {
1828 Range* ranges = new Range[num_ranges];
1829 for (int i = 0; i < num_ranges; i++) {
1830 ranges[i].start = Slice(range_start_key[i], range_start_key_len[i]);
1831 ranges[i].limit = Slice(range_limit_key[i], range_limit_key_len[i]);
1832 }
1833 Status s = db->rep->GetApproximateSizes(column_family->rep, ranges,
1834 num_ranges, sizes);
1835 if (!s.ok()) {
1836 SaveError(errptr, s);
1837 }
1838 delete[] ranges;
1839}

1841extern ROCKSDB_LIBRARY_API void rocksdb_approximate_sizes_cf_with_flags(
1842 rocksdb_t* db, rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* column_family,
1843 int num_ranges, const char* const* range_start_key,
1844 const size_t* range_start_key_len, const char* const* range_limit_key,
1845 const size_t* range_limit_key_len, uint8_t include_flags, uint64_t* sizes,
1846 char** errptr) {
1847 Range* ranges = new Range[num_ranges];
1848 for (int i = 0; i < num_ranges; i++) {
1849 ranges[i].start = Slice(range_start_key[i], range_start_key_len[i]);
1850 ranges[i].limit = Slice(range_limit_key[i], range_limit_key_len[i]);
1851 }
1852 Status s = db->rep->GetApproximateSizes(
1853 column_family->rep, ranges, num_ranges, sizes,
1854 static_cast<DB::SizeApproximationFlags>(include_flags));
1855 if (!s.ok()) {
1856 SaveError(errptr, s);
1857 }
1858 delete[] ranges;
1859}

1871void rocksdb_compact_range(rocksdb_t* db, const char* start_key,
1872 size_t start_key_len, const char* limit_key,
1873 size_t limit_key_len) {
1874 Slice a, b;
1875 db->rep->CompactRange(
1876 CompactRangeOptions(),
1877 // Pass nullptr Slice if corresponding "const char*" is nullptr
1878 (start_key ? (a = Slice(start_key, start_key_len), &a) : nullptr),
1879 (limit_key ? (b = Slice(limit_key, limit_key_len), &b) : nullptr));
1880}

1885 const char* limit_key, size_t limit_key_len) {
1886 Slice a, b;
1887 db->rep->CompactRange(
1888 CompactRangeOptions(), column_family->rep,
1889 // Pass nullptr Slice if corresponding "const char*" is nullptr
1890 (start_key ? (a = Slice(start_key, start_key_len), &a) : nullptr),
1891 (limit_key ? (b = Slice(limit_key, limit_key_len), &b) : nullptr));
1892}

1896 size_t limit_key_len, char** errptr) {

1899 db->rep,
1900 (start_key ? (a = Slice(start_key, start_key_len), &a) : nullptr),
1901 (limit_key ? (b = Slice(limit_key, limit_key_len), &b) : nullptr));

1903}

1952void rocksdb_flush_cfs(rocksdb_t* db, const rocksdb_flushoptions_t* options,
1953 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t** column_families,

1957 column_family_handles.push_back(column_families[i]->rep);
1958 }
1959
1960 SaveError(errptr, db->rep->Flush(options->rep, column_family_handles));
1961}

2088void rocksdb_writebatch_putv(rocksdb_writebatch_t* b, int num_keys,
2089 const char* const* keys_list,
2090 const size_t* keys_list_sizes, int num_values,
2091 const char* const* values_list,
2092 const size_t* values_list_sizes) {
2093 std::vector<Slice> key_slices(num_keys);
2094 for (int i = 0; i < num_keys; i++) {
2095 key_slices[i] = Slice(keys_list[i], keys_list_sizes[i]);
2096 }
2097 std::vector<Slice> value_slices(num_values);
2098 for (int i = 0; i < num_values; i++) {
2099 value_slices[i] = Slice(values_list[i], values_list_sizes[i]);
2100 }
2101 b->rep.Put(SliceParts(key_slices.data(), num_keys),
2102 SliceParts(value_slices.data(), num_values));
2103}

2275
2276class H : public WriteBatch::Handler {
2277 public:
2278 void* state_;
2279 void (*put_)(void*, const char* k, size_t klen, const char* v, size_t vlen);
2280 void (*deleted_)(void*, const char* k, size_t klen);
2281 void Put(const Slice& key, const Slice& value) override {
2282 (*put_)(state_, key.data(), key.size(), value.data(), value.size());
2283 }
2284 void Delete(const Slice& key) override {
2285 (*deleted_)(state_, key.data(), key.size());
2286 }
2287};
2288
2289class HCF : public WriteBatch::Handler {
2290 public:
2291 void* state_;
2292 void (*put_cf_)(void*, uint32_t cfid, const char* k, size_t klen,
2293 const char* v, size_t vlen);
2294 void (*deleted_cf_)(void*, uint32_t cfid, const char* k, size_t klen);
2295 void (*merge_cf_)(void*, uint32_t cfid, const char* k, size_t klen,
2296 const char* v, size_t vlen);
2297 Status PutCF(uint32_t column_family_id, const Slice& key,
2298 const Slice& value) override {
2299 (*put_cf_)(state_, column_family_id, key.data(), key.size(), value.data(),
2300 value.size());
2301 return Status::OK();
2302 }
2303 Status DeleteCF(uint32_t column_family_id, const Slice& key) override {
2304 (*deleted_cf_)(state_, column_family_id, key.data(), key.size());
2305 return Status::OK();
2306 }
2307 Status MergeCF(uint32_t column_family_id, const Slice& key,
2308 const Slice& value) override {
2309 (*merge_cf_)(state_, column_family_id, key.data(), key.size(), value.data(),
2310 value.size());
2311 return Status::OK();
2312 }
2313};
2314
2315void rocksdb_writebatch_iterate(rocksdb_writebatch_t* b, void* state,
2316 void (*put)(void*, const char* k, size_t klen,
2317 const char* v, size_t vlen),
2318 void (*deleted)(void*, const char* k,
2319 size_t klen)) {
2320 H handler;
2321 handler.state_ = state;
2322 handler.put_ = put;
2323 handler.deleted_ = deleted;
2324 b->rep.Iterate(&handler);
2325}
2326
2327void rocksdb_writebatch_iterate_cf(
2328 rocksdb_writebatch_t* b, void* state,
2329 void (*put_cf)(void*, uint32_t cfid, const char* k, size_t klen,
2330 const char* v, size_t vlen),
2331 void (*deleted_cf)(void*, uint32_t cfid, const char* k, size_t klen),
2332 void (*merge_cf)(void*, uint32_t cfid, const char* k, size_t klen,
2333 const char* v, size_t vlen)) {
2334 HCF handler;
2335 handler.state_ = state;
2336 handler.put_cf_ = put_cf;
2337 handler.deleted_cf_ = deleted_cf;
2338 handler.merge_cf_ = merge_cf;
2339 b->rep.Iterate(&handler);
2340}

2424void rocksdb_writebatch_wi_putv(rocksdb_writebatch_wi_t* b, int num_keys,
2425 const char* const* keys_list,
2426 const size_t* keys_list_sizes, int num_values,
2427 const char* const* values_list,
2428 const size_t* values_list_sizes) {
2429 std::vector<Slice> key_slices(num_keys);
2430 for (int i = 0; i < num_keys; i++) {
2431 key_slices[i] = Slice(keys_list[i], keys_list_sizes[i]);
2432 }
2433 std::vector<Slice> value_slices(num_values);
2434 for (int i = 0; i < num_values; i++) {
2435 value_slices[i] = Slice(values_list[i], values_list_sizes[i]);
2436 }
2437 b->rep->Put(SliceParts(key_slices.data(), num_keys),
2438 SliceParts(value_slices.data(), num_values));
2439}

2643
2644char* rocksdb_writebatch_wi_get_from_batch(rocksdb_writebatch_wi_t* wbwi,
2645 const rocksdb_options_t* options,
2646 const char* key, size_t keylen,
2647 size_t* vallen, char** errptr) {
2648 char* result = nullptr;
2649 std::string tmp;
2650 Status s = wbwi->rep->GetFromBatch(options->rep, Slice(key, keylen), &tmp);
2651 if (s.ok()) {
2652 *vallen = tmp.size();
2653 result = CopyString(tmp);
2654 } else {
2655 *vallen = 0;
2656 if (!s.IsNotFound()) {
2657 SaveError(errptr, s);
2658 }
2659 }
2660 return result;
2661}

2670 Slice(key, keylen), &tmp);

2673 result = CopyString(tmp);
2674 } else {
2675 *vallen = 0;
2676 if (!s.IsNotFound()) {
2677 SaveError(errptr, s);
2678 }
2679 }
2680 return result;
2681}

2730
2731void rocksdb_load_latest_options(
2732 const char* db_path, rocksdb_env_t* env, bool ignore_unknown_options,
2733 rocksdb_cache_t* cache, rocksdb_options_t** db_options,
2734 size_t* num_column_families, char*** list_column_family_names,
2735 rocksdb_options_t*** list_column_family_options, char** errptr) {
2736 DBOptions db_opt;
2737 std::vector<ColumnFamilyDescriptor> cf_descs;
2738 ConfigOptions config_opts;
2739 config_opts.ignore_unknown_options = ignore_unknown_options;
2740 config_opts.input_strings_escaped = true;
2741 config_opts.env = env->rep;
2742 Status s = LoadLatestOptions(config_opts, std::string(db_path), &db_opt,
2743 &cf_descs, &cache->rep);
2744 if (s.ok()) {
2745 char** cf_names = (char**)malloc(cf_descs.size() * sizeof(char*));
2746 rocksdb_options_t** cf_options = (rocksdb_options_t**)malloc(
2747 cf_descs.size() * sizeof(rocksdb_options_t*));
2748 for (size_t i = 0; i < cf_descs.size(); ++i) {
2749 cf_names[i] = strdup(cf_descs[i].name.c_str());
2750 cf_options[i] = new rocksdb_options_t{
2751 Options(DBOptions(), std::move(cf_descs[i].options))};
2752 }
2753 *num_column_families = cf_descs.size();
2754 *db_options = new rocksdb_options_t{
2755 Options(std::move(db_opt), ColumnFamilyOptions())};
2756 *list_column_family_names = cf_names;
2757 *list_column_family_options = cf_options;
2758 } else {
2759 *num_column_families = 0;
2760 *db_options = nullptr;
2761 *list_column_family_names = nullptr;
2762 *list_column_family_options = nullptr;
2763 SaveError(errptr, s);
2764 }
2765}
2766
2767void rocksdb_load_latest_options_destroy(
2768 rocksdb_options_t* db_options, char** list_column_family_names,
2769 rocksdb_options_t** list_column_family_options, size_t len) {
2770 rocksdb_options_destroy(db_options);
2771 if (list_column_family_names) {
2772 for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i) {
2773 free(list_column_family_names[i]);
2774 }
2775 free(list_column_family_names);
2776 }
2777 if (list_column_family_options) {
2778 for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i) {
2779 rocksdb_options_destroy(list_column_family_options[i]);
2780 }
2781 free(list_column_family_options);
2782 }
2783}

2837
2838void rocksdb_block_based_options_set_use_delta_encoding(

2978void rocksdb_set_options(rocksdb_t* db, int count, const char* const keys[],
2979 const char* const values[], char** errptr) {
2980 std::unordered_map<std::string, std::string> options_map;
2981 for (int i = 0; i < count; i++) {
2982 options_map[keys[i]] = values[i];
2983 }
2984 SaveError(errptr, db->rep->SetOptions(options_map));
2985}
2986
2987void rocksdb_set_options_cf(rocksdb_t* db,
2988 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* handle, int count,
2989 const char* const keys[],
2990 const char* const values[], char** errptr) {
2991 std::unordered_map<std::string, std::string> options_map;
2992 for (int i = 0; i < count; i++) {
2993 options_map[keys[i]] = values[i];
2994 }
2995 SaveError(errptr, db->rep->SetOptions(handle->rep, options_map));
2996}

3122rocksdb_logger_t* rocksdb_logger_create_stderr_logger(int log_level,
3123 const char* prefix) {
3124 rocksdb_logger_t* logger = new rocksdb_logger_t;
3125
3126 if (prefix) {
3127 logger->rep = std::make_shared<StderrLogger>(
3128 static_cast<InfoLogLevel>(log_level), prefix);
3129 } else {
3130 logger->rep =
3131 std::make_shared<StderrLogger>(static_cast<InfoLogLevel>(log_level));
3132 }
3133
3134 return logger;
3135}
3136
3137rocksdb_logger_t* rocksdb_logger_create_callback_logger(
3138 int log_level, void (*callback)(void*, unsigned, char*, size_t),
3139 void* priv) {
3140 rocksdb_logger_t* logger = new rocksdb_logger_t;
3141 logger->rep = std::make_shared<rocksdb_callback_logger_t>(
3142 static_cast<InfoLogLevel>(log_level), callback, priv);
3143 return logger;
3144}
3145
3146void rocksdb_logger_destroy(rocksdb_logger_t* logger) { delete logger; }

3302void rocksdb_options_enable_statistics(rocksdb_options_t* opt) {
3303 opt->rep.statistics = ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::CreateDBStatistics();
3304}
3305
3306void rocksdb_options_set_statistics_level(rocksdb_options_t* opt, int level) {
3307 if (!opt->rep.statistics) {
3308 return;
3309 }
3310
3311 if (level < rocksdb_statistics_level_disable_all) {
3312 level = rocksdb_statistics_level_disable_all;
3313 }
3314 if (level > rocksdb_statistics_level_all) {
3315 level = rocksdb_statistics_level_all;
3316 }
3317 opt->rep.statistics->set_stats_level(
3318 static_cast<ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::StatsLevel>(level));
3319}
3320
3321int rocksdb_options_get_statistics_level(rocksdb_options_t* opt) {
3322 if (!opt->rep.statistics) {
3323 return ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::StatsLevel::kDisableAll;
3324 }
3325
3326 return static_cast<int>(opt->rep.statistics->get_stats_level());
3327}

4047void rocksdb_options_set_plain_table_factory(
4048 rocksdb_options_t* opt, uint32_t user_key_len, int bloom_bits_per_key,
4049 double hash_table_ratio, size_t index_sparseness, size_t huge_page_tlb_size,
4050 char encoding_type, unsigned char full_scan_mode,
4051 unsigned char store_index_in_file) {
4052 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::PlainTableOptions options;
4053 options.user_key_len = user_key_len;
4054 options.bloom_bits_per_key = bloom_bits_per_key;
4055 options.hash_table_ratio = hash_table_ratio;
4056 options.index_sparseness = index_sparseness;
4057 options.huge_page_tlb_size = huge_page_tlb_size;
4058 options.encoding_type =
4059 static_cast<ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::EncodingType>(encoding_type);
4060 options.full_scan_mode = full_scan_mode;
4061 options.store_index_in_file = store_index_in_file;
4062
4063 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::TableFactory* factory =
4064 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::NewPlainTableFactory(options);
4065 opt->rep.table_factory.reset(factory);
4066}

4230rocksdb_ratelimiter_t* rocksdb_ratelimiter_create(int64_t rate_bytes_per_sec,
4231 int64_t refill_period_us,
4232 int32_t fairness) {
4233 rocksdb_ratelimiter_t* rate_limiter = new rocksdb_ratelimiter_t;
4234 rate_limiter->rep.reset(
4235 NewGenericRateLimiter(rate_bytes_per_sec, refill_period_us, fairness));
4236 return rate_limiter;
4237}
4238
4239rocksdb_ratelimiter_t* rocksdb_ratelimiter_create_auto_tuned(
4240 int64_t rate_bytes_per_sec, int64_t refill_period_us, int32_t fairness) {
4241 rocksdb_ratelimiter_t* rate_limiter = new rocksdb_ratelimiter_t;
4242 rate_limiter->rep.reset(NewGenericRateLimiter(rate_bytes_per_sec,
4243 refill_period_us, fairness,
4244 RateLimiter::Mode::kWritesOnly,
4245 true)); // auto_tuned
4246 return rate_limiter;
4247}
4248
4249rocksdb_ratelimiter_t* rocksdb_ratelimiter_create_with_mode(
4250 int64_t rate_bytes_per_sec, int64_t refill_period_us, int32_t fairness,
4251 int mode, bool auto_tuned) {
4252 rocksdb_ratelimiter_t* rate_limiter = new rocksdb_ratelimiter_t;
4253 rate_limiter->rep.reset(
4254 NewGenericRateLimiter(rate_bytes_per_sec, refill_period_us, fairness,
4255 static_cast<RateLimiter::Mode>(mode), auto_tuned));
4256 return rate_limiter;
4257}

4261}

4307uint64_t rocksdb_perfcontext_metric(rocksdb_perfcontext_t* context,
4308 int metric) {
4309 PerfContext* rep = context->rep;
4310 switch (metric) {
4311 case rocksdb_user_key_comparison_count:
4312 return rep->user_key_comparison_count;
4313 case rocksdb_block_cache_hit_count:
4314 return rep->block_cache_hit_count;
4315 case rocksdb_block_read_count:
4316 return rep->block_read_count;
4317 case rocksdb_block_read_byte:
4318 return rep->block_read_byte;
4319 case rocksdb_block_read_time:
4320 return rep->block_read_time;
4321 case rocksdb_block_checksum_time:
4322 return rep->block_checksum_time;
4323 case rocksdb_block_decompress_time:
4324 return rep->block_decompress_time;
4325 case rocksdb_get_read_bytes:
4326 return rep->get_read_bytes;
4327 case rocksdb_multiget_read_bytes:
4328 return rep->multiget_read_bytes;
4329 case rocksdb_iter_read_bytes:
4330 return rep->iter_read_bytes;
4331 case rocksdb_internal_key_skipped_count:
4332 return rep->internal_key_skipped_count;
4333 case rocksdb_internal_delete_skipped_count:
4334 return rep->internal_delete_skipped_count;
4335 case rocksdb_internal_recent_skipped_count:
4336 return rep->internal_recent_skipped_count;
4337 case rocksdb_internal_merge_count:
4338 return rep->internal_merge_count;
4339 case rocksdb_get_snapshot_time:
4340 return rep->get_snapshot_time;
4341 case rocksdb_get_from_memtable_time:
4342 return rep->get_from_memtable_time;
4343 case rocksdb_get_from_memtable_count:
4344 return rep->get_from_memtable_count;
4345 case rocksdb_get_post_process_time:
4346 return rep->get_post_process_time;
4347 case rocksdb_get_from_output_files_time:
4348 return rep->get_from_output_files_time;
4349 case rocksdb_seek_on_memtable_time:
4350 return rep->seek_on_memtable_time;
4351 case rocksdb_seek_on_memtable_count:
4352 return rep->seek_on_memtable_count;
4353 case rocksdb_next_on_memtable_count:

4440 return rep->env_link_file_nanos;

4443 case rocksdb_env_unlock_file_nanos:

4445 case rocksdb_env_new_logger_nanos:
4446 return rep->env_new_logger_nanos;
4447 case rocksdb_number_async_seek:
4448 return rep->number_async_seek;
4449 case rocksdb_blob_cache_hit_count:
4450 return rep->blob_cache_hit_count;
4451 case rocksdb_blob_read_count:
4452 return rep->blob_read_count;
4453 case rocksdb_blob_read_byte:
4454 return rep->blob_read_byte;
4455 case rocksdb_blob_read_time:
4456 return rep->blob_read_time;
4457 case rocksdb_blob_checksum_time:
4458 return rep->blob_checksum_time;
4459 case rocksdb_blob_decompress_time:
4460 return rep->blob_decompress_time;
4461 case rocksdb_internal_range_del_reseek_count:
4462 return rep->internal_range_del_reseek_count;
4463 case rocksdb_block_read_cpu_time:
4464 return rep->block_read_cpu_time;
4465 default:
4466 break;
4467 }
4468 return 0;
4469}

4484rocksdb_compactionfilter_t* rocksdb_compactionfilter_create(
4485 void* state, void (*destructor)(void*),
4486 unsigned char (*filter)(void*, int level, const char* key,
4487 size_t key_length, const char* existing_value,
4488 size_t value_length, char** new_value,
4489 size_t* new_value_length,
4490 unsigned char* value_changed),
4491 const char* (*name)(void*)) {
4492 rocksdb_compactionfilter_t* result = new rocksdb_compactionfilter_t;
4493 result->state_ = state;
4494 result->destructor_ = destructor;
4495 result->filter_ = filter;
4496 result->ignore_snapshots_ = true;
4497 result->name_ = name;
4498 return result;
4499}

4519
4520rocksdb_compactionfilterfactory_t* rocksdb_compactionfilterfactory_create(
4521 void* state, void (*destructor)(void*),
4522 rocksdb_compactionfilter_t* (*create_compaction_filter)(
4523 void*, rocksdb_compactionfiltercontext_t* context),
4524 const char* (*name)(void*)) {
4525 rocksdb_compactionfilterfactory_t* result =
4526 new rocksdb_compactionfilterfactory_t;
4527 result->state_ = state;
4528 result->destructor_ = destructor;
4529 result->create_compaction_filter_ = create_compaction_filter;
4530 result->name_ = name;
4531 return result;
4532}

4579
4580rocksdb_filterpolicy_t* rocksdb_filterpolicy_create_bloom_format(
4581 double bits_per_key, bool original_format) {
4582 // Make a rocksdb_filterpolicy_t, but override all of its methods so
4583 // they delegate to a NewBloomFilterPolicy() instead of user
4584 // supplied C functions.
4585 struct Wrapper : public rocksdb_filterpolicy_t {
4586 const FilterPolicy* rep_;
4587 ~Wrapper() override { delete rep_; }
4588 const char* Name() const override { return rep_->Name(); }
4589 const char* CompatibilityName() const override {
4590 return rep_->CompatibilityName();
4591 }
4592 // No need to override GetFilterBitsBuilder if this one is overridden
4593 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::FilterBitsBuilder* GetBuilderWithContext(
4594 const ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::FilterBuildingContext& context)
4595 const override {
4596 return rep_->GetBuilderWithContext(context);
4597 }
4598 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::FilterBitsReader* GetFilterBitsReader(
4599 const Slice& contents) const override {
4600 return rep_->GetFilterBitsReader(contents);
4601 }
4602 static void DoNothing(void*) {}
4603 };
4604 Wrapper* wrapper = new Wrapper;
4605 wrapper->rep_ = NewBloomFilterPolicy(bits_per_key, original_format);
4606 wrapper->state_ = nullptr;
4607 wrapper->destructor_ = &Wrapper::DoNothing;
4608 return wrapper;
4609}
4610
4611rocksdb_filterpolicy_t* rocksdb_filterpolicy_create_bloom_full(
4612 double bits_per_key) {
4613 return rocksdb_filterpolicy_create_bloom_format(bits_per_key, false);
4614}
4615
4616rocksdb_filterpolicy_t* rocksdb_filterpolicy_create_bloom(double bits_per_key) {
4617 return rocksdb_filterpolicy_create_bloom_format(bits_per_key, true);
4618}

4620rocksdb_filterpolicy_t* rocksdb_filterpolicy_create_ribbon_format(
4621 double bloom_equivalent_bits_per_key, int bloom_before_level) {
4622 // Make a rocksdb_filterpolicy_t, but override all of its methods so
4623 // they delegate to a NewRibbonFilterPolicy() instead of user
4624 // supplied C functions.
4625 struct Wrapper : public rocksdb_filterpolicy_t {
4626 const FilterPolicy* rep_;
4627 ~Wrapper() override { delete rep_; }
4628 const char* Name() const override { return rep_->Name(); }
4629 const char* CompatibilityName() const override {
4630 return rep_->CompatibilityName();
4631 }
4632 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::FilterBitsBuilder* GetBuilderWithContext(
4633 const ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::FilterBuildingContext& context)
4634 const override {
4635 return rep_->GetBuilderWithContext(context);
4636 }
4637 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::FilterBitsReader* GetFilterBitsReader(
4638 const Slice& contents) const override {
4639 return rep_->GetFilterBitsReader(contents);
4640 }
4641 static void DoNothing(void*) {}
4642 };
4643 Wrapper* wrapper = new Wrapper;
4644 wrapper->rep_ =
4645 NewRibbonFilterPolicy(bloom_equivalent_bits_per_key, bloom_before_level);
4646 wrapper->state_ = nullptr;
4647 wrapper->destructor_ = &Wrapper::DoNothing;
4648 return wrapper;
4649}

5448void rocksdb_ingest_external_file(

5450 const rocksdb_ingestexternalfileoptions_t* opt, char** errptr) {

5456}

5473rocksdb_slicetransform_t* rocksdb_slicetransform_create(
5474 void* state, void (*destructor)(void*),
5475 char* (*transform)(void*, const char* key, size_t length,
5476 size_t* dst_length),
5477 unsigned char (*in_domain)(void*, const char* key, size_t length),
5478 unsigned char (*in_range)(void*, const char* key, size_t length),
5479 const char* (*name)(void*)) {
5480 rocksdb_slicetransform_t* result = new rocksdb_slicetransform_t;
5481 result->state_ = state;
5482 result->destructor_ = destructor;
5483 result->transform_ = transform;
5484 result->in_domain_ = in_domain;
5485 result->in_range_ = in_range;
5486 result->name_ = name;
5487 return result;
5488}
5489
5490void rocksdb_slicetransform_destroy(rocksdb_slicetransform_t* st) { delete st; }
5491
5492struct SliceTransformWrapper : public rocksdb_slicetransform_t {
5493 const SliceTransform* rep_;
5494 ~SliceTransformWrapper() override { delete rep_; }
5495 const char* Name() const override { return rep_->Name(); }
5496 std::string GetId() const override { return rep_->GetId(); }
5497 Slice Transform(const Slice& src) const override {
5498 return rep_->Transform(src);
5499 }
5500 bool InDomain(const Slice& src) const override { return rep_->InDomain(src); }
5501 bool InRange(const Slice& src) const override { return rep_->InRange(src); }
5502 static void DoNothing(void*) {}
5503};
5504
5505rocksdb_slicetransform_t* rocksdb_slicetransform_create_fixed_prefix(
5506 size_t prefixLen) {
5507 SliceTransformWrapper* wrapper = new SliceTransformWrapper;
5508 wrapper->rep_ = ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::NewFixedPrefixTransform(prefixLen);
5509 wrapper->state_ = nullptr;
5510 wrapper->destructor_ = &SliceTransformWrapper::DoNothing;
5511 return wrapper;
5512}
5513
5514rocksdb_slicetransform_t* rocksdb_slicetransform_create_noop() {
5515 SliceTransformWrapper* wrapper = new SliceTransformWrapper;
5516 wrapper->rep_ = ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::NewNoopTransform();
5517 wrapper->state_ = nullptr;
5518 wrapper->destructor_ = &SliceTransformWrapper::DoNothing;
5519 return wrapper;
5520}

5629
5630void rocksdb_options_set_min_level_to_compress(rocksdb_options_t* opt,
5631 int level) {
5632 if (level >= 0) {
5633 assert(level <= opt->rep.num_levels);
5634 opt->rep.compression_per_level.resize(opt->rep.num_levels);
5635 for (int i = 0; i < level; i++) {
5636 opt->rep.compression_per_level[i] = ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::kNoCompression;
5637 }
5638 for (int i = level; i < opt->rep.num_levels; i++) {
5639 opt->rep.compression_per_level[i] = opt->rep.compression;
5640 }
5641 }
5642}

5694}

5696void rocksdb_delete_file_in_range(rocksdb_t* db, const char* start_key,
5697 size_t start_key_len, const char* limit_key,
5698 size_t limit_key_len, char** errptr) {
5699 Slice a, b;
5700 SaveError(
5701 errptr,
5702 DeleteFilesInRange(
5703 db->rep, db->rep->DefaultColumnFamily(),
5704 (start_key ? (a = Slice(start_key, start_key_len), &a) : nullptr),
5705 (limit_key ? (b = Slice(limit_key, limit_key_len), &b) : nullptr)));
5706}
5707
5708void rocksdb_delete_file_in_range_cf(
5709 rocksdb_t* db, rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* column_family,
5710 const char* start_key, size_t start_key_len, const char* limit_key,
5711 size_t limit_key_len, char** errptr) {
5712 Slice a, b;
5713 SaveError(
5714 errptr,
5715 DeleteFilesInRange(
5716 db->rep, column_family->rep,
5717 (start_key ? (a = Slice(start_key, start_key_len), &a) : nullptr),
5718 (limit_key ? (b = Slice(limit_key, limit_key_len), &b) : nullptr)));
5719}

5947rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* rocksdb_transactiondb_create_column_family(
5948 rocksdb_transactiondb_t* txn_db,
5949 const rocksdb_options_t* column_family_options,
5950 const char* column_family_name, char** errptr) {
5951 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* handle = new rocksdb_column_family_handle_t;
5952 SaveError(errptr, txn_db->rep->CreateColumnFamily(
5953 ColumnFamilyOptions(column_family_options->rep),
5954 std::string(column_family_name), &(handle->rep)));
5955 handle->immortal = false;
5956 return handle;
5957}
5958
5959rocksdb_transactiondb_t* rocksdb_transactiondb_open(
5960 const rocksdb_options_t* options,
5961 const rocksdb_transactiondb_options_t* txn_db_options, const char* name,
5962 char** errptr) {
5963 TransactionDB* txn_db;
5964 if (SaveError(errptr, TransactionDB::Open(options->rep, txn_db_options->rep,
5965 std::string(name), &txn_db))) {
5966 return nullptr;
5967 }
5968 rocksdb_transactiondb_t* result = new rocksdb_transactiondb_t;
5969 result->rep = txn_db;
5970 return result;
5971}
5972
5973rocksdb_transactiondb_t* rocksdb_transactiondb_open_column_families(
5974 const rocksdb_options_t* options,
5975 const rocksdb_transactiondb_options_t* txn_db_options, const char* name,
5976 int num_column_families, const char* const* column_family_names,
5977 const rocksdb_options_t* const* column_family_options,
5978 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t** column_family_handles, char** errptr) {
5979 std::vector<ColumnFamilyDescriptor> column_families;
5980 for (int i = 0; i < num_column_families; i++) {
5981 column_families.emplace_back(
5982 std::string(column_family_names[i]),
5983 ColumnFamilyOptions(column_family_options[i]->rep));
5984 }
5985
5986 TransactionDB* txn_db;
5987 std::vector<ColumnFamilyHandle*> handles;
5988 if (SaveError(errptr, TransactionDB::Open(options->rep, txn_db_options->rep,
5989 std::string(name), column_families,
5990 &handles, &txn_db))) {
5991 return nullptr;
5992 }
5993
5994 for (size_t i = 0; i < handles.size(); i++) {
5995 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* c_handle =
5996 new rocksdb_column_family_handle_t;
5997 c_handle->rep = handles[i];
5998 c_handle->immortal = false;
5999 column_family_handles[i] = c_handle;
6000 }
6001 rocksdb_transactiondb_t* result = new rocksdb_transactiondb_t;
6002 result->rep = txn_db;
6003 return result;
6004}

6008 rocksdb_snapshot_t* result = new rocksdb_snapshot_t;
6009 result->rep = txn_db->rep->GetSnapshot();
6010 return result;
6011}

6040rocksdb_t* rocksdb_transactiondb_get_base_db(rocksdb_transactiondb_t* txn_db) {
6041 DB* base_db = txn_db->rep->GetBaseDB();
6042
6043 if (base_db != nullptr) {
6044 rocksdb_t* result = new rocksdb_t;
6045 result->rep = base_db;
6046 return result;
6047 }
6048
6049 return nullptr;
6050}
6051
6052void rocksdb_transactiondb_close_base_db(rocksdb_t* base_db) { delete base_db; }
6053
6054rocksdb_transaction_t* rocksdb_transaction_begin(
6055 rocksdb_transactiondb_t* txn_db,
6056 const rocksdb_writeoptions_t* write_options,
6057 const rocksdb_transaction_options_t* txn_options,
6058 rocksdb_transaction_t* old_txn) {
6059 if (old_txn == nullptr) {
6060 rocksdb_transaction_t* result = new rocksdb_transaction_t;
6061 result->rep = txn_db->rep->BeginTransaction(write_options->rep,
6062 txn_options->rep, nullptr);
6063 return result;
6064 }
6065 old_txn->rep = txn_db->rep->BeginTransaction(write_options->rep,
6066 txn_options->rep, old_txn->rep);
6067 return old_txn;
6068}
6069
6070rocksdb_transaction_t** rocksdb_transactiondb_get_prepared_transactions(
6071 rocksdb_transactiondb_t* txn_db, size_t* cnt) {
6072 std::vector<Transaction*> txns;
6073 txn_db->rep->GetAllPreparedTransactions(&txns);
6074 *cnt = txns.size();
6075 if (txns.empty()) {
6076 return nullptr;
6077 } else {
6078 rocksdb_transaction_t** buf = (rocksdb_transaction_t**)malloc(
6079 txns.size() * sizeof(rocksdb_transaction_t*));
6080 for (size_t i = 0; i < txns.size(); i++) {
6081 buf[i] = new rocksdb_transaction_t;
6082 buf[i]->rep = txns[i];
6083 }
6084 return buf;
6085 }
6086}

6089 size_t name_len, char** errptr) {
6090 std::string str = std::string(name, name_len);
6091 SaveError(errptr, txn->rep->SetName(str));
6092}

6099}

6157
6158// Read a key inside a transaction
6159char* rocksdb_transaction_get(rocksdb_transaction_t* txn,
6160 const rocksdb_readoptions_t* options,
6161 const char* key, size_t klen, size_t* vlen,
6162 char** errptr) {
6163 char* result = nullptr;
6164 std::string tmp;
6165 Status s = txn->rep->Get(options->rep, Slice(key, klen), &tmp);
6166 if (s.ok()) {
6167 *vlen = tmp.size();
6168 result = CopyString(tmp);
6169 } else {
6170 *vlen = 0;
6171 if (!s.IsNotFound()) {
6172 SaveError(errptr, s);
6173 }
6174 }
6175 return result;
6176}
6177
6178rocksdb_pinnableslice_t* rocksdb_transaction_get_pinned(
6179 rocksdb_transaction_t* txn, const rocksdb_readoptions_t* options,
6180 const char* key, size_t klen, char** errptr) {
6181 rocksdb_pinnableslice_t* v = new (rocksdb_pinnableslice_t);
6182 Status s = txn->rep->Get(options->rep, Slice(key, klen), &v->rep);
6183 if (!s.ok()) {
6184 delete (v);
6185 if (!s.IsNotFound()) {
6186 SaveError(errptr, s);
6187 }
6188 return nullptr;
6189 }
6190 return v;
6191}

6253rocksdb_pinnableslice_t* rocksdb_transaction_get_pinned_for_update(
6254 rocksdb_transaction_t* txn, const rocksdb_readoptions_t* options,
6255 const char* key, size_t klen, unsigned char exclusive, char** errptr) {
6256 rocksdb_pinnableslice_t* v = new (rocksdb_pinnableslice_t);
6257 Status s = txn->rep->GetForUpdate(options->rep, Slice(key, klen),
6258 v->rep.GetSelf(), exclusive);
6259 v->rep.PinSelf();
6260 if (!s.ok()) {

6265 return nullptr;

6289
6290rocksdb_pinnableslice_t* rocksdb_transaction_get_pinned_for_update_cf(
6291 rocksdb_transaction_t* txn, const rocksdb_readoptions_t* options,
6292 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* column_family, const char* key, size_t klen,
6293 unsigned char exclusive, char** errptr) {
6294 rocksdb_pinnableslice_t* v = new (rocksdb_pinnableslice_t);
6295 Status s = txn->rep->GetForUpdate(options->rep, column_family->rep,
6296 Slice(key, klen), &v->rep, exclusive);
6297 if (!s.ok()) {
6298 delete (v);
6299 if (!s.IsNotFound()) {
6300 SaveError(errptr, s);
6301 }
6302 return nullptr;
6303 }
6304 return v;
6305}
6306
6307void rocksdb_transaction_multi_get(rocksdb_transaction_t* txn,
6308 const rocksdb_readoptions_t* options,
6309 size_t num_keys,
6310 const char* const* keys_list,
6311 const size_t* keys_list_sizes,
6312 char** values_list,
6313 size_t* values_list_sizes, char** errs) {
6314 std::vector<Slice> keys(num_keys);
6315 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_keys; i++) {
6316 keys[i] = Slice(keys_list[i], keys_list_sizes[i]);
6317 }
6318 std::vector<std::string> values(num_keys);
6319 std::vector<Status> statuses =
6320 txn->rep->MultiGet(options->rep, keys, &values);
6321 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_keys; i++) {
6322 if (statuses[i].ok()) {
6323 values_list[i] = CopyString(values[i]);
6324 values_list_sizes[i] = values[i].size();
6325 errs[i] = nullptr;
6326 } else {
6327 values_list[i] = nullptr;
6328 values_list_sizes[i] = 0;
6329 if (!statuses[i].IsNotFound()) {
6330 errs[i] = strdup(statuses[i].ToString().c_str());
6331 } else {
6332 errs[i] = nullptr;
6333 }
6334 }
6335 }
6336}

6431// Read a key outside a transaction
6432char* rocksdb_transactiondb_get(rocksdb_transactiondb_t* txn_db,
6433 const rocksdb_readoptions_t* options,
6434 const char* key, size_t klen, size_t* vlen,
6435 char** errptr) {
6436 char* result = nullptr;
6437 std::string tmp;
6438 Status s = txn_db->rep->Get(options->rep, Slice(key, klen), &tmp);
6439 if (s.ok()) {
6440 *vlen = tmp.size();
6441 result = CopyString(tmp);
6442 } else {
6443 *vlen = 0;
6444 if (!s.IsNotFound()) {
6445 SaveError(errptr, s);
6446 }
6447 }
6448 return result;
6449}

6456 Slice(key, klen), &v->rep);
6457 if (!s.ok()) {
6458 delete (v);
6459 if (!s.IsNotFound()) {
6460 SaveError(errptr, s);
6461 }
6462 return nullptr;
6463 }
6464 return v;
6465}

6754
6755rocksdb_optimistictransactiondb_t* rocksdb_optimistictransactiondb_open(
6756 const rocksdb_options_t* options, const char* name, char** errptr) {
6757 OptimisticTransactionDB* otxn_db;
6758 if (SaveError(errptr, OptimisticTransactionDB::Open(
6759 options->rep, std::string(name), &otxn_db))) {
6760 return nullptr;
6761 }
6762 rocksdb_optimistictransactiondb_t* result =
6763 new rocksdb_optimistictransactiondb_t;
6764 result->rep = otxn_db;
6765 return result;
6766}
6767
6768rocksdb_optimistictransactiondb_t*
6769rocksdb_optimistictransactiondb_open_column_families(
6770 const rocksdb_options_t* db_options, const char* name,
6771 int num_column_families, const char* const* column_family_names,
6772 const rocksdb_options_t* const* column_family_options,
6773 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t** column_family_handles, char** errptr) {
6774 std::vector<ColumnFamilyDescriptor> column_families;
6775 for (int i = 0; i < num_column_families; i++) {
6776 column_families.emplace_back(
6777 std::string(column_family_names[i]),
6778 ColumnFamilyOptions(column_family_options[i]->rep));
6779 }
6780
6781 OptimisticTransactionDB* otxn_db;
6782 std::vector<ColumnFamilyHandle*> handles;
6783 if (SaveError(errptr, OptimisticTransactionDB::Open(
6784 DBOptions(db_options->rep), std::string(name),
6785 column_families, &handles, &otxn_db))) {
6786 return nullptr;
6787 }
6788
6789 for (size_t i = 0; i < handles.size(); i++) {
6790 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* c_handle =
6791 new rocksdb_column_family_handle_t;
6792 c_handle->rep = handles[i];
6793 c_handle->immortal = false;
6794 column_family_handles[i] = c_handle;
6795 }
6796 rocksdb_optimistictransactiondb_t* result =
6797 new rocksdb_optimistictransactiondb_t;
6798 result->rep = otxn_db;
6799 return result;
6800}
6801
6802rocksdb_t* rocksdb_optimistictransactiondb_get_base_db(
6803 rocksdb_optimistictransactiondb_t* otxn_db) {
6804 DB* base_db = otxn_db->rep->GetBaseDB();
6805
6806 if (base_db != nullptr) {
6807 rocksdb_t* result = new rocksdb_t;
6808 result->rep = base_db;
6809 return result;
6810 }
6811
6812 return nullptr;
6813}
6814
6815void rocksdb_optimistictransactiondb_close_base_db(rocksdb_t* base_db) {
6816 delete base_db;
6817}
6818
6819rocksdb_transaction_t* rocksdb_optimistictransaction_begin(
6820 rocksdb_optimistictransactiondb_t* otxn_db,
6821 const rocksdb_writeoptions_t* write_options,
6822 const rocksdb_optimistictransaction_options_t* otxn_options,
6823 rocksdb_transaction_t* old_txn) {
6824 if (old_txn == nullptr) {
6825 rocksdb_transaction_t* result = new rocksdb_transaction_t;
6826 result->rep = otxn_db->rep->BeginTransaction(write_options->rep,
6827 otxn_options->rep, nullptr);
6828 return result;
6829 }
6830 old_txn->rep = otxn_db->rep->BeginTransaction(
6831 write_options->rep, otxn_options->rep, old_txn->rep);
6832 return old_txn;
6833}

6844 rocksdb_optimistictransactiondb_t* otxn_db) {

6846 delete otxn_db;

6848
6849rocksdb_checkpoint_t* rocksdb_optimistictransactiondb_checkpoint_object_create(
6850 rocksdb_optimistictransactiondb_t* otxn_db, char** errptr) {
6851 Checkpoint* checkpoint;
6852 if (SaveError(errptr, Checkpoint::Create(otxn_db->rep, &checkpoint))) {
6853 return nullptr;
6854 }
6855 rocksdb_checkpoint_t* result = new rocksdb_checkpoint_t;
6856 result->rep = checkpoint;
6857 return result;
6858}

6861
6862rocksdb_pinnableslice_t* rocksdb_get_pinned(
6863 rocksdb_t* db, const rocksdb_readoptions_t* options, const char* key,
6864 size_t keylen, char** errptr) {
6865 rocksdb_pinnableslice_t* v = new (rocksdb_pinnableslice_t);
6866 Status s = db->rep->Get(options->rep, db->rep->DefaultColumnFamily(),
6867 Slice(key, keylen), &v->rep);
6868 if (!s.ok()) {
6869 delete (v);
6870 if (!s.IsNotFound()) {
6871 SaveError(errptr, s);
6872 }
6873 return nullptr;
6874 }
6875 return v;
6876}
6877
6878rocksdb_pinnableslice_t* rocksdb_get_pinned_cf(
6879 rocksdb_t* db, const rocksdb_readoptions_t* options,
6880 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* column_family, const char* key,
6881 size_t keylen, char** errptr) {
6882 rocksdb_pinnableslice_t* v = new (rocksdb_pinnableslice_t);
6883 Status s = db->rep->Get(options->rep, column_family->rep, Slice(key, keylen),
6884 &v->rep);
6885 if (!s.ok()) {
6886 delete v;
6887 if (!s.IsNotFound()) {
6888 SaveError(errptr, s);
6889 }
6890 return nullptr;
6891 }
6892 return v;
6893}
6894
6895void rocksdb_pinnableslice_destroy(rocksdb_pinnableslice_t* v) { delete v; }
6896
6897const char* rocksdb_pinnableslice_value(const rocksdb_pinnableslice_t* v,
6898 size_t* vlen) {
6899 if (!v) {
6900 *vlen = 0;
6901 return nullptr;
6902 }
6903
6904 *vlen = v->rep.size();
6905 return v->rep.data();
6906}

6908// container to keep databases and caches in order to use
6909// ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::MemoryUtil
6910struct rocksdb_memory_consumers_t {
6911 std::vector<rocksdb_t*> dbs;
6912 std::unordered_set<rocksdb_cache_t*> caches;
6913};
6914
6915// initializes new container of memory consumers
6916rocksdb_memory_consumers_t* rocksdb_memory_consumers_create() {
6917 return new rocksdb_memory_consumers_t;
6918}
6919
6920// adds datatabase to the container of memory consumers
6921void rocksdb_memory_consumers_add_db(rocksdb_memory_consumers_t* consumers,
6922 rocksdb_t* db) {
6923 consumers->dbs.push_back(db);
6924}
6925
6926// adds cache to the container of memory consumers
6927void rocksdb_memory_consumers_add_cache(rocksdb_memory_consumers_t* consumers,
6928 rocksdb_cache_t* cache) {
6929 consumers->caches.insert(cache);
6930}
6931
6932// deletes container with memory consumers
6933void rocksdb_memory_consumers_destroy(rocksdb_memory_consumers_t* consumers) {
6934 delete consumers;
6935}
6936
6937// contains memory usage statistics provided by ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::MemoryUtil
6938struct rocksdb_memory_usage_t {
6939 uint64_t mem_table_total;
6940 uint64_t mem_table_unflushed;
6941 uint64_t mem_table_readers_total;
6942 uint64_t cache_total;
6943};
6944
6945// estimates amount of memory occupied by consumers (dbs and caches)
6946rocksdb_memory_usage_t* rocksdb_approximate_memory_usage_create(
6947 rocksdb_memory_consumers_t* consumers, char** errptr) {
6948 vector<DB*> dbs;
6949 for (auto db : consumers->dbs) {
6950 dbs.push_back(db->rep);
6951 }
6952
6953 unordered_set<const Cache*> cache_set;
6954 for (auto cache : consumers->caches) {
6955 cache_set.insert(const_cast<const Cache*>(cache->rep.get()));
6956 }
6957
6958 std::map<ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::MemoryUtil::UsageType, uint64_t> usage_by_type;
6959
6960 auto status = MemoryUtil::GetApproximateMemoryUsageByType(dbs, cache_set,
6961 &usage_by_type);
6962 if (SaveError(errptr, status)) {
6963 return nullptr;
6964 }
6965
6966 auto result = new rocksdb_memory_usage_t;
6967 result->mem_table_total = usage_by_type[MemoryUtil::kMemTableTotal];
6968 result->mem_table_unflushed = usage_by_type[MemoryUtil::kMemTableUnFlushed];
6969 result->mem_table_readers_total =
6970 usage_by_type[MemoryUtil::kTableReadersTotal];
6971 result->cache_total = usage_by_type[MemoryUtil::kCacheTotal];
6972 return result;
6973}
6974
6975uint64_t rocksdb_approximate_memory_usage_get_mem_table_total(
6976 rocksdb_memory_usage_t* memory_usage) {
6977 return memory_usage->mem_table_total;
6978}
6979
6980uint64_t rocksdb_approximate_memory_usage_get_mem_table_unflushed(
6981 rocksdb_memory_usage_t* memory_usage) {
6982 return memory_usage->mem_table_unflushed;
6983}
6984
6985uint64_t rocksdb_approximate_memory_usage_get_mem_table_readers_total(
6986 rocksdb_memory_usage_t* memory_usage) {
6987 return memory_usage->mem_table_readers_total;
6988}
6989
6990uint64_t rocksdb_approximate_memory_usage_get_cache_total(
6991 rocksdb_memory_usage_t* memory_usage) {
6992 return memory_usage->cache_total;
6993}
